Files to provide some options regarding Henkan and Muhenkan keys in Japanese keyboards.
To install, execute the following command:

$ sudo ./install.sh

The shell script copies two files jphenk and jpmuhen to the folder

/usr/share/X11/xkb/symbols/

and add appropriate settings to the file "/usr/share/X11/xkb/rules/evdev".
After the installation, the following options will get available:

- jphenk:rshift
- jphenk:rctrl
- jphenk:escape
- jphenk:ralt
- jpmuhen:lshift
- jpmuhen:lctrl
- jpmuhen:escape
- jpmuhen:lalt

You can write these options in "/org/gnome/desktop/input-sources/xkb-options" with, e.g., dconf.

